<font color="#FF0000">ADDENDUM</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jul 11 13:32:57 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Well, I did my homework, and that in the time frame you gave me the army division working that AO was the Americal Division supported by the 1/1 Amoured Cav (not 1st Cav affiliated)and others, hence the amtracks, APC's and tanks and other vehicles. Two tasks forces were happening in the time frame you spoke of. Task Force Barker and Task Force Miracle. There might have been others but I stopped here. The 1st Cav never worked around there. Americal Division worked up to and including Da Nang and all points west, in the same area you worked if I understand your posts on this and other threads correctly. According to their archives, part of the mission was to support 1st Marines (3/7 was mentioned).<br><br>
In my communique with one individual who was there with the Americal, he does not remember the particular ops I spesk of, but he remembers, &quot;.....I never saw anyone marching in the field, but on Russell Beach, big ass sweep of the Pinkville, every swinging dick that could walk, or ride, or drive a boat was on it. I did see Marines, tanks, APC's (marines and army), Navy swift boasts, Battleship New Jersey, and I don't know what the f____ all in that one. This was south of Chu Lai about 10 clicks.......&quot;<br><br>
Now that would have been something to gaze upon! :&gt;)<br><br>
About two weeks after your March 10th date, the 1st Cav Div, went into the Khe Sanh. Three weeks later, they went into the A Shau Valley. Previous to your date, they were entangled with NVA up in Thorn La Chu, Quang Tri and Hue and other hot spots.<br><br>
I communicated with other Marines who were there during Tet from the 1st and the name of Operation Rock jarred no memories. I also could not find any reference on this ops. But, I am a little more than curious and I would like to follow up on the ops and the after action reports if they are available. Do you have any sources with which you can direct me to?<br><br>
I am a bit envious that you were able to keep a journal of your experiences. I have long wished that I was able to do so. But, looking back, I had more then enough shit to hump on a day to day basis. Didn't even bother to carry letter writing stuff. Relied on bumming from the grunts for that.:) Especially in the time frame we speak. Memory is a terrible thing to rely on. <br><br>
Sorry to deviate from the purpose of this thread, but I am a stickler for being as factual as possible. As you well know, there are those who love to take some inaccurate or misleading crap and run away with it for their own ends.
